This paper deals with unsupervised image-to-image translation, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper introduces a discriminator with dilated convolutions, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with shape deformation, which is a topic that falls under computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
